{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The request sent to the external API always includes the complete list of valid taxonomy labels.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Rationale A (failure boundary): this checks cross-module handoff from request construction to API client payload; a pure unit test of a helper can miss wiring bugs where taxonomy is dropped before send. Rationale B (higher-level gate): behavior text is about what is \"sent to the external API,\" but it does not require real network/OS nor real model judgment. Rejected System because the behavior does not require real HTTP conditions, only payload inspection at the client boundary. Rejected Agentic because correctness is payload composition, not model output quality.","test_description":"Wire classifier module with a fake/stub API client, invoke classify(document,taxonomy), and assert captured outbound request contains the full taxonomy label list exactly as configured.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When the API returns a label that is not in the taxonomy, the module returns \"unknown\" instead of forwarding the unexpected value to the caller.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"Rationale A (failure boundary): this is local validation/normalization logic on returned label membership. Rationale B (higher-level gate): no real infra and no real model decision needed; deterministic fixtures fully reproduce failure. Rejected Integration because behavior can be exercised at one function/object boundary with raw API label input and taxonomy set.","test_description":"Call normalization/response-mapping logic with taxonomy {legal,technical,financial,other} and raw label \"medical\"; assert final label is \"unknown\".","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.85,"Integration":0.12,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"For identical raw API responses, the module's normalization step always produces the same final label.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"Rationale A (failure boundary): this is determinism/idempotence of normalization function for identical inputs. Rationale B (higher-level gate): behavior explicitly scopes to \"raw API responses\" and \"normalization step,\" which disqualifies infra/model requirements. Rejected Integration because no module handoff is required to expose nondeterministic normalization bug.","test_description":"Invoke normalization twice (or many times) with the same raw response fixture and taxonomy; assert identical final label every run.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.9,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"On repeated live API calls for the same document and taxonomy, the returned label remains consistent unless the provider response itself changes.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Rationale A (failure boundary): behavior explicitly requires repeated live AI-provider calls; stubs cannot reveal provider/model-driven variance. Rationale B (higher-level gate): correctness depends on real AI API outputs over repeated runs, so deterministic mock responses would hide real inconsistency failures. Rejected Workflow because this is a single agentic decision repeated, not multiple agentic stages in sequence.","test_description":"Run N repeated real provider classifications for fixed document+taxonomy, record provider raw responses and module final labels, and assert label changes only when raw provider response changes.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.03,"System":0.12,"Agentic":0.83,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"Request construction enforces the configured token budget before