"When the API signals that the request rate is too high, the module waits and retries rather than returning an error to the caller.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Rationale A (failure boundary): retry behavior is orchestration across client adapter, backoff/wait policy, and retry loop state. Rationale B (higher-level gate): can be reproduced with stubbed API responses (e.g., 429 then success) and controllable clock; real network/OS not required. Rejected System because failure mode is retry orchestration logic, not real transport quirks. Rejected Agentic because outcome does not depend on model output quality.","test_description":"Use fake API client to return rate-limit error then success, with fake clock/backoff hooks; assert module waits per policy, retries, and returns successful label instead of propagating immediate error.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.78,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.0}}]}
